cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is about universal style transfer, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new method that involves feature transforms, which is related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely. The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method, which suggests that it involves some form of optimization or learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also generates stylized images and synthesizes textures, which suggests that it involves multimedia processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves visualizing features, which suggests that it involves graphics and visualization, making cs.GR (Graphics) another possible sub-category.
